5-Step Meditation Progression for the New Year Yogi Explains

5 Steps For the New Year!

Forrest Knutson

Jan 2, 2026
View in app

Good morning, dear yogis!

Its a new year, and I wanted to put together the five steps for those who are new to meditation:

  • HRV-Resonance Breathing

  • Sit Very Still

  • Notice the Four Proofs

  • OM Japa in the chakras

  • Enjoy

This heart of meditation allows us to enter the low-idle state a million timesuntil we become so accustomed to living in the parasympathetic that, when stress arrives, we ask ourselves: Why this tension? Why this sympathetic arousal?

Youll still go down that road again and again, until the burden of unnecessary sympathetic activation feels so pointless that you simply cant engage it without a truly life-and-death reason.

As you live more and more in the parasympathetic, the Freeze Response will visit you in meditation with increasing frequency. That is pratyahara, and out of it dharana will ariseclarity. Downloads will happen in this clarity.

You will touch the right brain, and you will know things. Some downloads will be small. Some will be, Oh yeah, I knew that, but now you feel it deeply. Others will rock your world and make you a brand-new person.

A life of parasympathetic dominance brings emerging clarity, and out of that clarity you will glimpse the Higher Self. A sense of It will enter your life more and more. The old feeling of living life alone will slowly fade. Synchronicities will begin to dominate, and you will learn to listen to the whispers of your soul.

Thats the yogic progression as it blossoms in life. I hope youll take it by the hand and make it your guide for this new year. Print it out and place it where you can see it. Let it lead you within.

Ashokji once told me his only job was to get me to the medulla so I could Google God.
Thats what this is.

Love to you, dear family. I wish you every success in the New Year!
